  "text": "If the future reactor neutrino experiments will confirm the current bestfit point, therefore, some new physics will be required in order to reconcile the presence of the light sterile neutrino in the early Universe with the current observations. Such new physics may be in the form of new interactions (see e.g. [CITATION_1] ), preventing the thermalization of the new neutrino thanks to the presence of additional matter effects, which suppress neutrino oscillations between the active and the sterile states at the relevant times.",
